01:00:58,360 --> 01:01:14,019
[SPEAKER_01] I think at that moment, there was such a, I was just so grief, grief stricken, because I realized I saw myself as a child, as a little girl standing before God at the end of my life.

699
01:01:14,099 --> 01:01:21,980
[SPEAKER_01] But for some reason, I was seeing myself as a child, which I think, you know, is significant.

700
01:01:21,980 --> 01:01:28,340
[SPEAKER_01] But, but I was seeing myself as a child standing before God and him saying, Ramona, did you know?

701
01:01:28,340 --> 01:01:30,019
[SPEAKER_01] And what did you do?

702
01:01:30,019 --> 01:01:38,860
[SPEAKER_01] And I think at those words, what did you do is when I realized that I had for three years, been complicit in the deaths of innocent babies.

703
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:47,320
[SPEAKER_01] For three years, I tried to defend my position that, oh, I'm just referring women for abortion.

704
01:01:47,320 --> 01:01:50,900
[SPEAKER_01] It's their choice, whether they do it, whether they don't do it.

705
01:01:50,900 --> 01:01:52,099
[SPEAKER_01] That's not on me.

706
01:01:52,099 --> 01:01:54,880
[SPEAKER_01] I'm not responsible for what they choose.

707
01:01:55,639 --> 01:02:07,500
[SPEAKER_01] And it was in that moment that I realized that I was responsible, because at the end of the day, it didn't, it, while it mattered what a woman chose, yes, she has the free will to choose.

708
01:02:07,500 --> 01:02:18,920
[SPEAKER_01] But I also was responsible for not defending life, even if that resulted in the abortion of those babies, that I still had to defend life.

709
01:02:20,119 --> 01:02:32,019
[SPEAKER_01] And I think that was that fight, that moment where I realized that this euphemism of choice, a woman's right to choose, is simply just a euphemism.

710
01:02:32,019 --> 01:02:43,400
[SPEAKER_01] You know, it is, it is words to get us to be distracted from the reality of what is abortion, because we don't want to say abortion, a woman's right to choose abortion.

711
01:02:43,400 --> 01:02:47,860
[SPEAKER_01] We just call it choice, or we call it reproductive health care, right?

712
01:02:47,860 --> 01:02:52,780
[SPEAKER_01] Or just, you know, health care in general, right?

713
01:02:52,780 --> 01:03:04,420
[SPEAKER_01] We use all of these euphemisms to try to make abortion more palatable for us to be more accepting of what it is, because we want to ignore what abortion really is.

714
01:03:05,019 --> 01:03:18,440
[SPEAKER_01] And I think I really had spent all of my life buying into the lie of choice, and being deceived by those words, pro-choice, and a woman's right to choose.

715
01:03:18,440 --> 01:03:22,059
[SPEAKER_01] I had spent all of my life being deceived by those words.

716
01:03:22,480 --> 01:03:32,840
[SPEAKER_01] And it was in that moment I realized, yeah, I have blood on my hands, because I was helping women obtain abortions.

717
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:36,719
[SPEAKER_01] I was very complicit in that.

718
01:03:37,099 --> 01:03:49,480
[SPEAKER_01] And when you, when you come to that moment in your life where you realize what you've been involved in, and in this case, the death of human beings, the innocent, the most innocent among us, right?

719
01:03:49,480 --> 01:03:57,239
[SPEAKER_01] It is very hard, very, very difficult, very painful to accept that reality.

720
01:03:57,239 --> 01:04:03,139
[SPEAKER_01] And yet, at the same time, it was also such a beautiful moment of God's mercy.

721
01:04:03,920 --> 01:04:15,179
[SPEAKER_01] And as much as it hurt me, as much as I was broken, heartbroken, there was also this beautiful moment where I felt God's love very, very deeply in that moment.

722
01:04:15,179 --> 01:04:17,579
[SPEAKER_01] So it wasn't like I was being scolded.

723
01:04:17,579 --> 01:04:20,920
[SPEAKER_01] It was that God was saying, I love you.

724
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:25,079
[SPEAKER_01] And I love you so much that you have to see what you've done.

725
01:04:25,079 --> 01:04:27,639
[SPEAKER_01] And it was beautiful.

726
01:04:27,639 --> 01:04:28,820
[SPEAKER_01] It was a beautiful moment.

727
01:04:28,820 --> 01:04:37,900
[SPEAKER_01] And I do, I knew right then, that, that would apply to everything in my life.

728
01:04:37,900 --> 01:04:40,300
[SPEAKER_01] What did you do?

729
01:04:40,300 --> 01:04:43,400
[SPEAKER_01] You know, what did you do when your neighbor was thirsty?

730
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:45,719
[SPEAKER_01] What did you do when your neighbor was hungry?

731
01:04:45,719 --> 01:04:48,840
[SPEAKER_01] You know, what did you do when someone needed clothing?

732
01:04:49,119 --> 01:04:54,900
[SPEAKER_01] You know, all of those things that we turn away from, you know, that we didn't do the right thing.

733
01:04:54,900 --> 01:04:59,360
[SPEAKER_01] That I would always be held accountable for what I did and what I didn't do.

734
01:05:00,380 --> 01:05:09,559
[SPEAKER_01] And I think, you know, just moving forward from that, I realized that my life would never be the same from that moment on.

735
01:05:09,559 --> 01:05:17,820
[SPEAKER_01] And so I dried off my tears and I went in the house and I just began to cry again.

736
01:05:18,260 --> 01:05:22,880
[SPEAKER_01] And my husband, God bless him, he was frightened because he thought, what is going on, you know?

737
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:26,139
[SPEAKER_01] And I just fell into his arms and I began to cry.

738
01:05:26,139 --> 01:05:27,380
[SPEAKER_01] And I said, I'm going to go to hell.

739
01:05:27,380 --> 01:05:28,980
[SPEAKER_01] And he said, no, you're not.

740
01:05:28,980 --> 01:05:30,639
[SPEAKER_01] No, you're not.

741
01:05:30,639 --> 01:05:32,179
[SPEAKER_01] And he comforted me.

742
