791
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:08,159
[SPEAKER_01] And I was not familiar with any of the feast days or even what that meant.

792
01:08:08,159 --> 01:08:10,940
[SPEAKER_01] It was May the 1st, 2011.

793
01:08:10,940 --> 01:08:12,320
[SPEAKER_01] I'll never forget the date.

794
01:08:12,320 --> 01:08:17,819
[SPEAKER_01] Today is the anniversary of that Divine Mercy Sunday.

795
01:08:17,819 --> 01:08:19,960
[SPEAKER_01] Yes, May the 1st, 2011.

796
01:08:19,960 --> 01:08:23,199
[SPEAKER_01] I didn't know what that meant.

797
01:08:23,199 --> 01:08:35,399
[SPEAKER_01] But also, it was also the date of the beatification of St. John Paul II, who we know to be, was the most staunch defender and outspoken defender of life.

798
01:08:35,399 --> 01:08:39,579
[SPEAKER_01] And so no coincidence there at all.

799
01:08:39,579 --> 01:08:56,239
[SPEAKER_01] I was sitting in Mass with my family and throughout the entire Mass, I was just praying to God to help me, to give me some insight, something, some sign, anything to help me do what I needed to do.

800
01:08:56,479 --> 01:08:59,659
[SPEAKER_01] And give me the strength and give me the strength and the grace to take a leap of faith.

801
01:08:59,659 --> 01:09:07,000
[SPEAKER_01] And he spoke to me throughout the entire Mass, through the scriptures, through the songs, through the hymns, everything.

802
01:09:07,000 --> 01:09:18,479
[SPEAKER_01] And it was during the moment of consecration of the Eucharist that it was such a powerful moment.

803
01:09:18,479 --> 01:09:24,479
[SPEAKER_01] Because, you know, as Catholics, we are always taught about the true presence of Jesus in the Eucharist.

804
01:09:24,479 --> 01:09:36,300
[SPEAKER_01] And this is why this moment led me to understand not just the reality of that, but also to really finally understand Jesus on the cross.

805
01:09:36,300 --> 01:09:43,439
[SPEAKER_01] And so it was during the consecration of the Eucharist that I heard God say very clearly to me.

806
01:09:43,439 --> 01:09:51,659
[SPEAKER_01] It was when the priest was lifting up the host that I heard God say, Ramona, have faith in me.

807
01:09:51,659 --> 01:09:52,420
[SPEAKER_01] I forgive you.

808
01:09:53,140 --> 01:09:54,600
[SPEAKER_01] And I began to cry.

809
01:09:54,600 --> 01:10:02,659
[SPEAKER_01] And it was such a very audible, you know, like, I can't even explain it.

810
01:10:02,659 --> 01:10:04,159
[SPEAKER_01] You know, just so clear.

811
01:10:04,159 --> 01:10:05,539
[SPEAKER_01] Ramona, I forgive you.

812
01:10:05,539 --> 01:10:06,340
[SPEAKER_01] Have faith in me.

813
01:10:06,340 --> 01:10:09,579
[SPEAKER_01] And I cried.

814
01:10:09,579 --> 01:10:14,460
[SPEAKER_01] And I just knew at that moment what God was saying, you know, to trust.

815
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:23,039
[SPEAKER_01] And that's with me not knowing anything about divine mercy, not even knowing that the words, Jesus, I trust in you, are written on the image.

816
01:10:23,140 --> 01:10:24,340
[SPEAKER_01] I knew nothing of that.

817
01:10:24,340 --> 01:10:26,760
[SPEAKER_01] I didn't even know that what that image meant.

818
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:28,079
[SPEAKER_01] You know, I'd seen it.

819
01:10:28,079 --> 01:10:28,840
[SPEAKER_01] I never knew.

820
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:35,260
[SPEAKER_01] And so he was calling me to trust him and to take a leap of faith.

821
01:10:35,659 --> 01:10:41,739
[SPEAKER_01] And so when we walked out of mass that day, I knew, I knew I couldn't, I couldn't go on.

822
01:10:42,220 --> 01:10:43,880
[SPEAKER_01] And I had Monday off.

823
01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:53,680
[SPEAKER_01] So we were only open three days a week, which is really incredible because the number three is very significant throughout my story and just in my whole life in general.

824
01:10:54,359 --> 01:10:59,180
[SPEAKER_01] We worked, I worked at Planned Parenthood three days a week and we, I was there three years.

825
01:10:59,180 --> 01:11:05,539
[SPEAKER_01] On the third day of the 40 Days for Life campaign, I went and asked for prayers and we had three children at the time.

826
01:11:05,539 --> 01:11:07,060
[SPEAKER_01] I was 33 years old.

827
01:11:07,060 --> 01:11:10,640
[SPEAKER_01] Very significant.

828
01:11:11,920 --> 01:11:18,399
[SPEAKER_01] But I, I, I went back to work, what we were closed on Mondays and we're open Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday.

829
01:11:18,399 --> 01:11:27,060
[SPEAKER_01] And so on Monday, I was just very, I had so much peace because I knew I was going to quit.

830
01:11:27,060 --> 01:11:32,680
[SPEAKER_01] I didn't know exactly when I had in my mind at the end of the month, but I had so much peace.

831
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:35,600
[SPEAKER_01] And then on Tuesday, I had to go back to work.

832
01:11:35,600 --> 01:11:41,199
[SPEAKER_01] And I remember just getting up that day, just feeling so much dread, like, oh, I don't want to go, you know?

833
01:11:41,199 --> 01:11:44,880
[SPEAKER_01] And I thought, okay, I'm going to quit this week.

834
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:46,539
[SPEAKER_01] I'm, this is going to be it.

835
01:11:46,539 --> 01:11:48,960
[SPEAKER_01] I'm not going to, I'm not going to go after this.

836
01:11:48,960 --> 01:12:02,500
[SPEAKER_01] And so on my drive to work, I was praying to God to protect me in those final three days from all occasions of sin, from any referrals for abortion.

837
01:12:02,680 --> 01:12:17,960
